content:
@MoonshotQuest I can confirm too, it's laggy on iPhone X but only the first time :/

It's very frustrating mostly when you have a lot animations like your app (very nice btw ✌️). Many users get an idea of the first screens of an application so this issue is probably, in my opinion, the most critical I see on Flutter 🥺

I added a lot of animations before this issue but now I try to add as little as possible in order to promise a smooth experience (very frustrating 😩)

@mellowcello77 

I don't do any tricks like that.. but try to adhere to [performance best practices](https://flutter.dev/docs/perf/rendering).

But i believe my app is yanky on older iOS devices.

@masterlonghorn  You could also look at this demo project made by @danReynolds  to demonstrate jank:

https://github.com/danReynolds/iosjank

If you could show how to use your method with this demo example (if its harder to share your real code), that'd be really helpful too
